{"questionId":"5275194","questionHtml":"<p>A nucleus of platinum (Pt) undergoes alpha decay to form an osmium (Os) nucleus as represented by the following reaction.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mmultiscripts><mi>Pt</mi><mprescripts></mprescripts><mn>78</mn><mn>175</mn></mmultiscripts></math>&nbsp;→ Os + alpha particle</p>\n<p>What are the number of protons and the number of neutrons in the osmium nucleus?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height:162px;border-color:#000000;width:382px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:46px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:153.333px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Number of protons</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:159.667px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Number of neutrons</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:46px;\">A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:153.333px;text-align:center;\">74</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.667px;text-align:center;\">93</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:46px;\">B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:153.333px;text-align:center;\">76</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.667px;text-align:center;\">93</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:46px;\">C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:153.333px;text-align:center;\">74</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.667px;text-align:center;\">95</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:46px;\">D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:153.333px;text-align:center;\">76</td>\n<td style=\"width:159.667px;text-align:center;\">95</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275194","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.24","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A nucleus of platinum (Pt) undergoes alpha decay to form an osmium (Os) nucleus as represented by the following reaction. Pt78175 → Os + alpha particle What are the number of proto","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"24","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadc